title: NJ-11 Special Election Democratic Primary Candidates Guide
intro_html:
11 candidates are running in the Feb. 5 special Democratic primary election to fill New Jersey's 11th congressional district seat, previously held by now-governor Mikie Sherrill.

The Democratic candidate who wins the February special primary will appear on a special general election ballot on Apr. 16 against the sole Republican candidate to determine who will complete Sherrill's term through January 2027.
